-- Lufthansa Says European Flight Yields No Better Than in `Crisis Year' 2009
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2010-10-11T09:43:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/lufthansa-says-european-flight-yields-no-better-than-in-crisis-year-2009.html
Deutsche Lufthansa AG’s average
yield on European flights is “still at or below the level of
the crisis year 2009,” management board member Stefan Lauer
said, according to the company’s employees magazine.  Margins are still well below the level needed for
investments in the airline’s fleet, the publication,
Lufthanseat, quoted Lauer as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
